    "details": {
      "blurb": "Bloatmage seneschal of Castle Korvosa (A44)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "infernal",
          "thassilonian"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 15
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (A44):</strong> the bloatmage <strong>seneschal</strong> — Ileosa's vault-keeper and the castle's arcane warden, grotesquely swollen with leeched blood, and <strong>possessed for years by @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.sermignattoDvl01]{Sermignatto}</strong>, who wears him as a public face (his sketchbooks compulsively repeat a three-faced worm — @Check[type:occultism|dc:30] names a belier devil). He drew the Mushfens map filed in A43; his spellbooks (A44 secret panel) hold the akaruzug formulas. <strong>Morale:</strong> below ~30 HP he <em>dimension doors</em> to A59 — Sermignatto's lair — for a last stand. <strong>If slain</strong> he smiles and whispers thanks, freed. <strong>If the possession is broken without killing him, he surrenders:</strong> he reveals Sermignatto's history and habits (A59), confirms the queen's contract lies in A90, and explains the A77 phase door; once Sermignatto is dead he collects his spellbooks (if the PCs left them) and quits Korvosa forever.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
